Ondo state government on Tuesday, trained commercial motorcycle (Okada) and tricycle (Keke) riders on safety measures and rules. The special adviser to the governor on transport, Mr Tobi Ogunleye, in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), said the training was the fifth in the series. Mr Ogunleye said the drivers and riders institute in the state had trained several riders and drivers on safety measures to ensure safety on the roads. Also speaking with NAN, director of vehicle inspection services in the state, Mr Alaba Adeleye, said the training was to impart knowledge into the Okada riders on the dos and donâ€™ts of riding. (NAN)